## 🔧 **Technical Implementation Guide**

### **A. Getting Started**
```bash
# Installation (works on any system)
curl -s https://angeh.lang/install | bash

# Basic usage
angeh --help                    # Show available commands
angeh --create project.angeh    # Start new project
angeh --run program.angeh       # Execute program
angeh --share project.angeh     # Share with community
```

### **B. Development Workflow**
```angeh
# Create simple community program
🔴🤝 ⚪🔗 🟢👥 → "Help connect people"

# Add complexity gradually
🔴🤝 ⚪🔗 🟢👥 ⚪➕ 🔴🌱 → "Help connect people and grow together"

# Test with community
🟢👥 ⚪🔍 ⚪🔗 🔴✅ → "People examine with approval"
```

### **C. Best Practices**
```
1. Start Simple: Begin with 1-2 dot patterns
2. Test Locally: Verify with your community first
3. Iterate Together: Include community feedback
4. Scale Gradually: Add complexity only when needed
5. Preserve Culture: Respect local knowledge systems
6. Monitor Impact: Track community wellbeing metrics
```

